# Pinned reference for Benchmark v2 arm P (the "pinned" arm).
#
# This is the single, authoritative place the pin lives. Bumping the pin is a
# one-line change here, committed as an annotated dashboard event (a pin bump is
# a real, recorded change in the H/P ratio trend — see plan section 3 and
# open decision 3).
#
# Value MUST be an existing tagged release of this repo whose GitHub release
# publishes the plugin zip asset. arm P bakes in the IMMUTABLE RELEASED artifact
# for this tag (downloaded from the release, sha256-verified against the release
# digest) — it is NOT rebuilt from the tag. A rebuild would drift with toolchain
# changes (gradle/JDK/deps) and move the H/P ratio for non-connector reasons; the
# released jar is the fixed reference. The verified sha256 is recorded in the
# image provenance (provenance.json + OCI label).
#
# Policy (plan open decision 3): the pinned reference = the last tagged release,
# bumped only deliberately. To bump: set the value below to the new tag, commit
# with a message noting the old->new tags and the reason.
#
# Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored; the first non-comment,
# non-blank line is the pinned ref.
